# Imperative core: functions, bindings, loops, collections, interpolation.

## To native args () -> Seq of Text
## To native parseInt (s: Text) -> Int

## To qs (arr: Seq of Int, lo: Int, hi: Int) -> Seq of Int:
    If lo is at least hi:
        Return arr.
    Let pivot be item hi of arr.
    Let mutable result be arr.
    Let mutable i be lo.
    While i is less than hi:
        If item i of result is at most pivot:
            Set item i of result to item hi of result.
        Set i to i + 1.
    Return qs(result, lo, i - 1).

## Main
Let arguments be args().
Let n be parseInt(item 2 of arguments).
Let mutable arr be a new Seq of Int with capacity n.
Let mutable seed be 42.
While seed is less than n:
    Set seed to (seed * 1103515245 + 12345) % 2147483648.
    Push (seed / 65536) % 32768 to arr.
Let m be a new Map of Text to Int.
Set m at "answer" to 42.
Let total be length of arr.
Show "sorted {total} items, first is {seed:.2}".
Show "" + item 1 of arr + " " + checksum.
